{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2014}} {{Use Hong Kong English|date=April 2014}} {{Infobox film | name = All About Love | image = All About Love 2010 poster.jpg | alt = | caption = Theatrical release poster | director = [[Ann Hui]] | producer = {{Plainlist| * Ann Hui * Angela Wong * [[Wong Jing]] }} | screenplay = Yang Yeeshan | based on = | starring = {{Plainlist| * [[Sandra Ng]] * [[Vivian Chow]] }} | music = Anthony Chue | cinematography = Charlie Lam | editing = {{Plainlist| * Chan Chi-wai * Eric Kong Chi-leung }} | production companies = Class Limited | distributor = Mega-Vision Pictures | released = {{Film date|df=yes|2010|8|11|Hong Kong Summer International Film Festival|2010|8|26|Hong Kong}} | runtime = 105 minutes | country = Hong Kong | language = Cantonese | budget = }} '''''All About Love''''' (得閒炒飯 ''De xian chao fan'') is a 2010 Hong Kong film directed and produced by [[Ann Hui]]. Based on a true story, the plot concerns two [[lesbian]]s who had been lovers in the past and meet again years later in a counseling session for expectant mothers.<ref name=movieweb>{{Cite web|last=Philbrick|first=Jami|title=Exclusive: Director Ann Hui Talks All About Love|url=http://www.movieweb.com/news/exclusive-director-ann-hui-talks-all-about-love|website=[[MovieWeb]]|date=22 October 2010|accessdate=23 September 2011}}</ref> Hui said in an interview that initially "There were no investors" for the film because the subject of same-sex relationships was banned in China, and the Hong Kong film industry relied on the Chinese market.<ref name=movieweb />
Ms. Hui, a graduate of the [[London Film School]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Hui, Ann|url=https://hkwomenfilmmakers.wordpress.com/hui-ann-2/|website=Hong Kong Women Filmmakers|date=2017|accessdate=25 April 2018}}</ref> described the film as "serious...but it is also very commercial," adding that "Sometimes it is better to make serious issues more acceptable to audiences, by making it a comedy and having big stars so that people will come watch the movie."<ref>{{cite web|last1=Seno|first1=Alexandra A.|title=Hong Kong: A Love Story|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424052748704206804575466811054922440|work=[[The Wall Street Journal]]|date=3 September 2010|accessdate=14 January 2016}}</ref>
