'''Erica Armah Bra-Bulu Tandoh''' popularly known as ''[[Disc jockey|DJ]] Switch'' (born {{circa}} 2008) is a [[Ghanaian]] school girl who is also a DJ and advocate of education.

In June 2018, Erica became the youngest person to win Ghana's annual DJ award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.businessinsider.com/dj-switch-viral-10-year-old-musician-from-ghana-2018-6?IR=T|title=The internet is obsessed with DJ Switch, a 10-year-old musician from Ghana who is more talented than you will ever be|publisher=}}</ref> In September 2018, she has opened the [[Bill & Melinda Gates Foundation|Bill and Melinda Gates' Foundation's]] annual Goalkeepers event in [[New York City|New York]], as the warm up act to [[President of France|French President]] [[Emmanuel Macron]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2018/09/28/africa/dj-switch/index.html|title=Meet the 10-year-old DJ from Ghana who just wowed world leaders|last=CNN|first=Melissa Mahtani Video by Samantha Guff and Janelle Davis,|work=CNN|access-date=2018-10-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2018/jun/30/meet-dj-switch-the-10-year-old-drawing-crowds-in-ghana-video|title=Meet DJ Switch, the 10-year-old drawing crowds in Ghana – video|last=Bullock|first=James|date=2018-06-30|work=The Guardian|access-date=2018-10-09|last2=Rao|first2=Akshata|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077|last3=Roberts|first3=Simon|last4=credited|first4=Source: DJ Switch YouTube/Ghana Music/As}}</ref>

