'''Jenna Bans''' is an [[United States|American]] [[screenwriter]]. Originally hired as a staff writer for [[Jerry Bruckheimer]]'s cancelled action series ''[[Fearless (TV pilot)|Fearless]]'', Bans became a part of the crew of ''[[Desperate Housewives]]'' in 2004. In 2006 she was nominated for a Writers Guild of America Award for the screenplay to the ''Desperate Housewives'' episode "[[Next (Desperate Housewives episode)|Next]]" and in 2007 she received another nomination for the episode "[[It Takes Two (Desperate Housewives)|It Takes Two]]". Bans co-wrote both episodes together with [[Kevin Murphy (screenwriter)|Kevin Murphy]]. Bans is a producer and writer on ''[[Grey's Anatomy]]'', and is the creator and the co-producer (along with [[Shonda Rhimes]]) of ''[[Off the Map (TV series)|Off the Map]]'', a series which premiered on ABC in January 2011, and was cancelled on May 13, 2011. From 2012 to 2014, she was the regular writer and co-executive producer on another [[Shonda Rhimes]] created drama, [[Scandal (TV series)|Scandal]], on ABC.
In 2014, Bans created pilot ''Sea of Fire'' for ABC. In 2015, she created ''[[The Family (2016 TV series)|The Family]]'', also for ABC.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/scandals-jenna-bans-sells-political-735907|title='Scandal's' Jenna Bans Sells Political Thriller to ABC|author=Lesley Goldberg|work=The Hollywood Reporter|accessdate=1 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2015/01/flesh-blood-drama-jenna-bans-pilot-abc-1201362113/|title=‘Flesh & Blood’ Mystery Drama From Jenna Bans Gets ABC Pilot Order - Deadline|author=Nellie Andreeva|work=Deadline|accessdate=1 March 2015}}</ref>
Bans is the creator and executive producer of the NBC series ''[[Good Girls (TV series)|Good Girls]]'', which began broadcasting on February 26, 2018.<ref name= "goodgirls">{{cite news |last=Birnbaum |first=Debra |url= https://variety.com/2018/tv/news/good-girls-jenna-bans-donald-trump-1202674831/ |title=‘Good Girls’ Creator Jenna Bans on How Donald Trump’s Election Fueled Her |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=February 19, 2018 |accessdate=March 20, 2018}}</ref>
